    "text": "For the one-dimensional Keller-Segel system with parameter \( m \le -1 \), all solutions emanating from suitably regular initial data are globally bounded, indicating the absence of a critical mass phenomenon.",
    "topic": "Absence of critical mass in 1D Keller-Segel"
  },
  {
    "text": "For certain parabolic-elliptic simplifications of the system, the absence of a critical mass phenomenon holds for all \( m \in (-\infty, -1] \cup (0, \infty) \).",
    "topic": "Absence of critical mass in simplified 1D Keller-Segel"
  },
  {
    "text": "If the initial datum is monotone, the absence of a critical mass phenomenon extends to all real \( m \) in the one-dimensional setting.",
    "topic": "Absence of critical mass with monotone initial data"
  },
  {
    "text": "The boundedness of the energy functional from below, the embedding \( W^{1,1} \hookrightarrow L^\infty \), and the spatially non-degenerate parabolic nature of the mass accumulation function are key features enabling the absence of critical mass in one dimension.",
    "topic": "One-dimensional features preventing critical mass"
  },
  {
    "text": "In higher-dimensional domains, critical mass phenomena are known to occur for critical quasilinear Keller-Segel systems, contrasting with the one-dimensional case discussed.",
    "topic": "Contrast with higher-dimensional Keller-Segel"
  }
